ğŸ‘¤ What is an Object?

An object is an instance of a class.
Memory is allocated only when an object is created, not when the class is defined.

ğŸ“„ Think of:
	â€¢	ğŸ§¾ Class: JEE Application Form Template
	â€¢	ğŸ§ Object: A form filled and submitted by a student
Each student â†’ One object based on the same class.

